The paper deals with the security analysis of an audio data encryption scheme, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The scheme uses DNA encoding and key chaining algorithm, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and communication engineering (cs.CE) concepts. The encryption scheme is applied to audio data, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the scheme can be used for information security in various systems, which involves system engineering (cs.SY) concepts.
